RBAC follows hierarchical scope inheritance:

Management Group
→ Subscription
→ Resource Group
→ Resource

Permissions assigned higher in the hierarchy flow downward unless restricted.

For example, Reader at subscription level applies to all contained resource groups.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is enterprise-wide governance.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is broad audit access.

Hierarchy simplifies large-scale permission management.
